race.comment: HE'SGOTTHESAY (3) was dominant breaking his maiden here last start, putting a big gap on rivals over this trip. Progressive type who looks well placed to go right on with it. IONACELTIC (7) was no match for a smart winner last time but stuck on well for second after scoring at Dalby prior. Consistent and capable of bouncing back into the winner's stall. LUCONI (6) disappointed last time but his first two runs back were full of merit. Long time between drinks but worth another chance. FITZROY STREET (9) produced a strong late run into the frame last start and still has upside. Wide draw is tricky but Wiggins is a key booking.
